  "steps": [
    {
      "title": "Drill Holes with Spade Bit",
      "body": "Cut boards according to cut list and drill holes in the 8- 1X3’s @ 26”and the 6-1X3’s @ 24”. Use the 3/8” spade bit for this step.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/c80b186fe5c01ec0.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Drill Pocket Holes",
      "body": "Drill pocket holes in the 6- 1X3 @ 24”. This is what the shelf boards will attach to. You will only need two pocket holes per board to support the shelf board sections.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/2cf617370aeb682a.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Sand and Stain",
      "body": "Completely sand your boards and paint or stain. This is very difficult to do once the table is assembled."
    },
    {
      "title": "Make Shelf Units",
      "body": "Lay 2- 1X2 @ 17.5” boards across 7- 1X3 @ 18” boards and screw together with 1 ¼” wood screws. Make three of these.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/deeb739ff3b872fb.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Build Leg Units",
      "body": "Place 3-1X3 @ 24” between 2- 1X3 @ 26” Secure with a bolt, washer, and hex nut. The holes drilled with the spade bit will be the placement of the boards. tighten nuts to ensure stability of the table. Make two leg units.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/4690216d2bf14552.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Attach Shelves to Leg Units",
      "body": "Take the shelf sections you have already assembled and attach to the leg units with pocket hole screws. The shelf units should hang over 1” on each side.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/e0af07dccb8c2a04.webp"
    }
  ],
